{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Of particular interest to BC4LLMs, and arguably the most fundamental component within a blockchain, the consensus protocol is the governing system that controls how data is added to a blockchain's ledger.",
    "At its core is the consensus mechanism, which both ensures the validity of proposed data and fosters an environment of accountability, so that nodes submitting invalid information may be penalized accordingly.",
    "For example, the Proof of Work (PoW) consensus mechanism [82] is by far the most widely known.",
    "In it, nodes must solve a complex mathematical equation in order to gain rights to propose data for the blockchain.",
    "When such a node submits new data, it is scrutinized by every other node in the system."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, the Proof of Work (PoW) consensus mechanism [82] is by far the most widely known."
  ]
}